1.title: Next
1.content: For the next trial press the Continue button.

2.title: Instruction Screen H
2.content:
In this task, you will be asked to remember a series of digits, in the order that they were presented to you.
Please close any other applications on your device, and please put away and silence your cell phone.
It is important to minimize any distractions in your environment, so that you can concentrate on this task.
Begin this task when you know that you have at least 30 minutes of uninterrupted time to complete it.
Please do not take your headphones off, and please do not adjust the volume until the study is completed.
It is important that you follow the instructions, as the data will be published as part of a research project.
Please press the 'Continue' button to continue.

items.title: Thank you for completing the task.

items.label: 1. Did you have any help from another person when remembering the digits?
2. Did you use any external help (e.g., paper and pencil) to remember the digits?
3. Did you say the digits aloud when trying to remember them?
4. Did you turn off the volume on your headphones during the task?
5. Did you remove or unplug your headphones during the task?

7. While you were completing the study, were there any external sources of visual or auditory distraction (e.g., other people speaking in the same room, a running video, a song playing in the background, etc.)?
7b. If Yes, what was the source of distraction?
8. What equipment did you use to do the experiment?

items.title: Thank you for completing the task.

items.label: 9. What type of headphones did you use to play the sounds?
10. What device did you use to record your responses?
11. How motivated were you to obtain the best test-score possible?
12. How concentrated were you on the task?
13. When performing the task were you switching between different tasks or browsers?
14. Did you experience any technical difficulties during the study (e.g., problems with the internet connection, delays in presentation, etc)?
15. What is the current time at your location (please specify am or pm)?
16. If you reported that you have hearing loss at the start of the study, please tell us more about this now.

5.title: Debrief Screen
5.content:
Background Sound and Short-term Memory

Thank you for taking part in our research study, your time is very much appreciated. The research you have just taken part in aims to investigate how an individual's short-term memory is affected by the presence of background sound that they attempt to ignore. In this task you attempted to memorize sequences of numbers that were sometimes presented with background sound. We are interested in whether the presence of that sound makes short-term memory performance better, or worse.

You will never be identified in any findings of this experiment nor will it be possible to link the findings back to you. We would like to remind you that this is the final opportunity to withdraw your data from the experiment. If you wish to withdraw, simply close your browser.

By clicking the confirm button, below, you are submitting your response and accepting that you can no longer withdraw.
Please press the 'Confirm' button to continue.

9.content:

When you have chosen , please click Done to continue.

35.title: Recall
35.content:
Please select the numbers you just saw, in the order they were presented.
When you have chosen all you can recall, please click Done to continue.

43.title: Get-set-go
43.content:
Ready?

In a moment, we're going to show you a sequence of digits. Please try to remember them as best you can, you'll be asked to recall them immediately after, in the order in which they were presented. Please concentrate on remembering the digits, and ignore any sounds that you hear through the headphones. The sounds are completely irrelevant to the task. Please do not speak the digits aloud. It is important that you remain quiet.

When you're ready, please press Continue below.

metadata.title: Headphone screening
metadata.description:
This study implements the headphone screening procedure as described by Woods et al. (2017).

Woods, K. J., Siegel, M. H., Traer, J., & McDermott, J. H. (2017). Headphone screening to facilitate web-based auditory experiments. Attention, Perception, & Psychophysics, 79(7), 2064–2072.

45.title: Introduction
45.content:
Sound calibration

You must wear headphones
during this study!

If you are not already wearing headphones,
please put some on before continuing.

Click below after you have fitted your headphones
to start the calibration.

messageHandlers.code:
this.internals.calibrationClip = new Audio()
this.internals.calibrationClip.src = this.files['noise_calib_stim.wav']
this.internals.calibrationClip.load()

this.options.events['click a'] = function(e) {
  e.preventDefault()
  this.internals.calibrationClip.play()
}

47.title: Volume calibration
47.content:
Sound calibration

We will now calibrate
the volume of your headphones.

Please take through the following steps to calibrate your headphones:

  1. Set your computer volume to about 25% of its maximum level.
  2. Click here to listen to a calibration sound. Turn up the volume on your computer until the calibration sound is at a loud but comfortable level. You can listen to it as many times as you like.

Click below once you have set the computer volume to a loud but comfortable level

52.title: Task instructions
52.content:
Sound calibration

In the following, you will hear several sequences of three sounds each, separated by silence. Your task is to judge which of these was the softest or quietest.

We will ask you for your judgement after each sequence of three sounds. The sounds will only be played once, so please pay close attention.

Click below to start the task.

messageHandlers.title: Analyse task

55.title: Sounds
55.content:
Please listen carefully
to the sounds

The study will progress automatically

56.title: Judgement
56.content:
Which of the three sounds was the softest (quietest)?

Please make your choice by clicking on one of the buttons.

57.title: Loop rerun offer
57.content:
Sound calibration

You have failed the calibration test.
Please try again, making sure you have set
your headphones to a stereo setting.
You could also try increasing the volume.
You may take the calibration test up to 5 times.

58.title: Trap
58.content:
Sorry!

Your system does not provide the audio fidelity required to complete this study.

We are very sorry, but you cannot continue
with this study.

59.title: Thanks
59.content:
Thank you!

You have successfully completed
the calibration task.

Please click below to continue with the study.
